<br>
But it amuses me that Vegans and animal activist are often pro - choice.  Its not ok to kill and eat the cows or chickens, but its ok to rip apart/kill a fetus that may have thoughts and feelings like any other full term baby.<br>
<br>
As far as the distinction goes, I am anti-abortion in most situations (see above), but I have a harder time with abortions that take place after the fetus has formed its own systems.  I also think that many girls who seek abortion are not given enough information about the development of the fetus.  It is dehumanized to a lump of cells which after a very short time is NOT true.  Here in Utah, a girl/woman who wants to have an abortion is required to recieve information about the stages of development, including pictures.  I applaud that.  I havent talked to many woman who have been completely at peace with their decision to have an abortion.  Most that I have talked to have regrets.  <br>
<br>
I think one way to avoid that is make sure that they get educated.<br>
<br>
Raz. - I know that my kids had thoughts and feelings prior to being born.  Its not a light switch.  Why is it OK to extingusih that life prior to birth and then at one second after birth it is murder.  That is a very thin line. --Shirene <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mightyk>MightyK</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#3333ff>(1/11/03 2:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: life</span><hr size=1> I feel once it is viable outside of the womb (24/25 weeks) the option of a non-medical abortion should be stopped. And I believe it is. <br>
<br>
You can not have a law that makes exceptions like rape incest or other such thing. How would a woman prove it was incest? How humilating. And rape. . . Its hard enough knowing that others might not believe you were violated in the most basic and horrific way, and already there is the thought that you are dirty and unclean and those thoughts stay with you for such a long time. But can you imagine, if you were denied the abortion because you can't prove it having that constant growing reminder inside of you? You would NEVER be able to escape that rape for the next 9 months. Every time you couldn't even roll over in bed, or have to pee every ten minutes, its a reminder of what some sick bastard did to you. It makes me sick to think about. Its also one of the reasons I have trouble with that florida law. To me just one person going through that is too much.<br>
<br>
And would that person even take care of themselves during those 9 months? Self-loathing after being raped is common. That can bring on some self-destructive behaviors. Its an effort to take good care of yourself even when you want the pregnancy. But I can't see what the motivation would be if it was brought on by rape. So prenatal care would be poor. AND that is something else to consider. The costs of having a baby. Pregnancy is not cheap in anyway. <br>
<br>
I know you say you believe in abortion for rape. BUT if you attempt to limit abortions to those who can some way prove rape, you would be condemning people such as myself who could not prove it. I have a history of depression, I do not know if I could have handled that. I don't think I could. And family would want to know who the father is... my father would probably have been tempted to go out hunting for the bastard. And then there would be the judging of people who would assume I was easy and loose because I wasn't married. Or stupid (which I was). <br>
<br>
You can't arbituarily decide who could and can't have abortions because it would always leave someone who needs it for their very sanity on the other side. And FORCING her to carry a child brought on by rape would be like raping her over and over and over for the next 9 months. And beyond because it can take months for your body to recover from childbearing and birth. Only this time it isn't just one man doing it to her. But the whole country. <br>
<br>
