There are plenty of reasons why people become irresponsible. Some are just plain stupid. Do we really want just plain stupid people having more children? Cruel yeah but frankly I'm tired of hearing about children dying in cars because of the mothers stupidity. Or being left abandoned in trashcans. Left alone because the mother is too young to be responsible. Left addicted to crack because the mother couldn't give it up. <br>
<br>
After my rape I was irresponsible. I went through a time where I just stopped saying no. Hell someone already didn't listen and held me down and took it any way. I didn't ever want to go through that again, so I stopped saying no. Sure condoms were always used, being a willing participant I could at least assure that. But condoms can break. I wasn't in my right mind during that time. I know alot of people who have acted like that for my reasons, and for other reasons. I don't know if pregnancy would have snapped me out of that, or just snapped me. I didn't even think of pregnancy at that point. I was so numb.<br>
<br>
I am just trying to say that its not just people thinking, &quot;oh well if I get pregnant I can always abort&quot;. Teens are especially bad at not thinking about the consequences of sex. Shit, teens are good about not thinking of the consequences of anything. They think they can fly and they can't. <br>
<br>
But I also don't think it matters what we think. We can never be in their shoes and understand. Maybe it is selfish... but perhaps by being selfish they are saving a child a miserible life, or birth defects because the woman would be selfish during pregnancy and contoinue bad habits.<br>
