Mormongirl, you are entitled to your beliefs. If you feel abortion is wrong, don't have one. Try to influence your sister or friend not to have one, for that matter. But don't try to legislate your spiritual beliefs - because you don't know what's best for the rest of us.<br>
<br>
I've noticed that it's very easy to be pro-life, right up until you actually need an abortion yourself. And don't kid yourself that it'll never happen to you, because that's exactly what I used to think. Married, using birth control, and so on. Why would I ever need an abortion? But you know what, when I did need one those rights were available to me. And IF 2nd trimester abortion had been outlawed in my state, it wouldn't have been available to me. And my baby would have suffered. Because believe me, as reasonable as my abortion was, their are pro-lifers all over the place who condemn my choice because they belief ANY life, no matter how painful or compromised, ANY child, no matter how disabled, must be born because they believe it's &quot;God's Will.&quot;<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
