<br>
The fetus could be separate from the mom at some point, but cannot survive without the mom (host) before a certain point, so isn't a classic example of two separate beings, but rather a parasitic relationship.<br>
<br>
And the whole &quot;I think therefore I am&quot;, Descartes point...fetuses do not have organized brain wave oatterns (what neurologists recognize as &quot;consciousness&quot;) until the third trimester. They have some electrical charges  prior to that, but nothing that is the same as a mature infant until then.<br>
<br>
Just wanted to make those two points....<br>
